 absorption observed in the CW\ntransmission/absorption measurements. Notably regardless of interchanging\ncomponents, the slow cooling of carriers in metal-halide perovsites shows\nlittle effect of GammaLO, ELO, and Eex. As such, here it is proposed: while the\ninitial cooling of carriers is attributed to LO phonons, the overall cooling of\ncarriers is dominated by the intrinsic low thermal conductivity of all\nmetal-halide perovskites which limits the dissipation of acoustic phonons in\nthese systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Mar 2021 18:12:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 01:58:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-22"}
