ons at different Reynolds and Richardson\nnumbers and quantify the variations in velocity and pressure fields. The\nresults in this paper indicate that the proposed deep learning technique can\nbecome a promising direction in experimental fluid mechanics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 03:12:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 Mar 2021 19:20:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-07"}
