and p-moments\n$\\mathbb{E}[\\![|\\widehat{u(x,t)}|^{p}]\\!] $ are derived. Since $\\lim_{t\\uparrow\n\\infty}\\mathbb{E}[\\![|\\widehat{u(x,t)}|^{p}]\\!]=0 $, the Cauchy evolution of\nthe randomly perturbed solution is stable since the heat equation smooths out\nor dissipates volatility induced by initial data randomness as\n$t\\rightarrow\\infty$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 03:44:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 13 Jun 2021 22:53:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-15"}
