ight]^2}\\right]^{1/2}M_\\odot {\\rm pc^{-1}}$, where\n$\\lambda_{0,max}(N)$ represents the maximum line-mass of the non-magnetized\nfilament and $\\Phi_{cl}$ indicates one-half of the magnetic flux threading the\nfilament per unit length. Although the negative-indexed polytrope makes the\nmaximum line-mass decrease compared with that of the isothermal model, a\nmagnetic field threading the filament increases the line-mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 05:52:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Jun 2021 11:30:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-04"}
